Get Ready With Me! 

Lilo lost control of her bladder and bowels when she became paralyzed with IVDD in 2012. We change her diaper at least 4-6x everyday.Whatever doesn’t come out naturally, must be manually expressed! This is what works for us! She wears an XS pet diaper by Vet’s Best for lighter volume (2-4 hours), and a size S for heavier volume (4+ hours/overnight). During the day while we’re home, she’ll also wear an outer diaper to collect any accidental poops 😆 This separation-combo also helps reduce risk of UTI (especially for females). When we are not home (or for overnight), she uses the Drag Bag! It helps keeps things tucked in, and makes morning cleanup extra easy!!

Sleeping Bootie 👸🏻

July is IVDD Awareness Month, and I’m just popping in to remind you that my life matters. My life is wheelie cool! My life is extraordinary. Sometimes I wonder if I’ll wake up from this beautiful dream. I’ve lived with this scary disease for almost 11 years. To my fellow IVDD survivors: stay strong and brave. Let your mama & papa know that you want to fight this 💪🏼🙏🏼🦾

$2K later, her diagnosis is: SENIOR DOG 😩 

Lilo Health Update: for most of July, Lilo was having a digestive crisis (no appetite, vomiting, diarrhea & bloody stool), on top of her pre-existing conditions (CHF, UTI). Poor little grandma was miserable and had no energy or drive. Despite her tender age of 16, she was just not herself. After a 2nd set of labs, X-rays, and urinalysis…we discovered NOTHING 🥹 No major issues seen on her scans, slight elevation in liver, kidney, and pancreatic levels, and an ongoing, stubborn UTI. They switched up her antibiotics, and after a few days our [almost] 16yo princess is back to her spicy self, and is eating well again 🙏🏼 We’ve become regulars at the Vets office this past year 🫣

When Seniors have an appetite. 

After changing up LILO’s antibiotics, her appetite came back as well 🙏🏼 Our current regimen includes a variation of cod, salmon, chicken, scrambled eggs, and a small portion of brown rice or plain pasta. For supplements, she gets a mix of: Pumpkin powder, RoseHip Vital Canine, Synacore, and Manuka Honey (together, it helps settle her tummy & gives her a boost in immunity & supports joint health).

What a Wonderful World 🤍

It is known that pets miss their humans tremendously when they’re left home alone. But I say I miss LILO more than that! We set up the first spy-cam in 2012 when Lilo fell ill to #IVDD. I would watch her endlessly to make sure she was OK. And 11 years later, I’m doing the same! However, watching her sleep, drink water, whine/bark - brings me comfort now for some reason. She is more than OK. She is alive and beating the odds every single day. Approaching our 11th year with IVDD is beyond humbling. We thank our followers (both old & new) for coming along on this journey with us ♿️

This is my #IVDD story ♿️ Intervertebral Disc Disease struck me hard, and I became paralyzed at the youthful age of 5. My parents and I were extremely scared. Social Media wasn’t a place to find resources/info back in 2012, so we learned everything on our own, and followed all the recommendations from @dodgerslist (DodgersList.com). IVDD affects 1 in 4 Dachshunds, and it’s not just a progressive genetic condition, but may also be brought on by an acute injury. I got my cart by @eddieswheels 3 months after my surgery, while I was still doing physical therapy. Once we were comfortable with IVDD aftercare, and things were looking brighter, I started my IG and FB pages in 2014. November marks my 11th year with IVDD. To share my story to people all over the world is beyond COOL and humbling. Thank you for spending your time here 🫶🏽

Still falling in love with this one 🤍

This week marks 11 years since #IVDD crashed into our lives. What an unpredictable and extraordinary journey has been. We could not be more proud of our girl Lilo. Her happiest place is always next to me - even when I’m washing my face and brushing my teeth. Cherishing these sweet moments, because one day I will look down and she won’t be there. I’m so thankful for this little chicken nugget, my little shadow, my baby girl 🙏🏼
